  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "By including personalized data such as genetic markers and real-time behavioral feedback, AI systems can become more precise and adaptive in gustatory analysis.",
    "One promising approach involves incorporating genetic variations in taste receptor genes (e.g., TAS2R38 polymorphisms (Nolden and Feeney 2020)) into AI predictive models.",
    "These genetic differences lead to diverse reactions to basic tastes like bitterness and sweetness, complicating universal flavor recommendations.",
    "Mapping genetic markers to AI taste predictions helps identify subgroups needing tailored formulations (Daviet and Nave 2024), such as low-bitterness nutritional supplements or specifically flavored protein drinks for individuals highly sensitive to bitter tastes.",
    "Metabolic and physiological data can also significantly improve personalization."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Mapping genetic markers to AI taste predictions helps identify subgroups needing tailored formulations (Daviet and Nave 2024), such as low-bitterness nutritional supplements or specifically flavored protein drinks for individuals highly sensitive to bitter tastes."
